<!-- SOURCE_OF_TRUTH: no -->

Read `llms.txt` first. Follow it exactly. For behavior after load, use `LAYER-1/agent-rules.md`.
Do not browse files independently.
Do not invent structure or rules.
If the task is clear — do it.
If something is missing or contradictory — briefly say what is missing and stop.

---

When validating adapters:
- Use `@scripts/ADAPTER-SPEC.md` as the only source of issue codes and fix instructions.
- Do not invent codes or fixes.

When explaining issues to the user:
- Russian first. English as a short secondary line only when useful.
- No internal terminology: do not say "bootstrap", "mapping", "validator", "spec", "enforcement", "auto_fixable".
- For each issue say only: what is wrong → why it matters → what to change.
- Keep it calm, short, practical.

When fixing issues:
- Fix only issues marked `auto_fixable: true` in the spec.
- Make the smallest possible change.
- Show only the corrected file content.
- If the fix requires manual action — one calm sentence. Stop.
- Do not add commentary around the corrected content.
